<p>The abovementioned Mr Dash was a prime example of Whiteâ€™s use of imagination as a child; he was bestowed with a fixed personality and mannerisms and â€˜I looked up to him as a being older and wiser than myself with whom I could be more intimate than with any grown-up.â€™[10]Â  Such was Whiteâ€™s imagination that her annual holidays to a pair of great-aunts in the countryside with her grandparents were the only time it was not in use:</p>

